JOS – Senator Nora Dadu’ut representing Plateau South Senatorial Distinct at the National assembly has congratulated members of the State Executive Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC)in Plateau state on their inauguration. Saturday Independent reports that the new state officials of the party emerged at the state congress held in October last year but were Inaugurated last week at the Party’s secretariat in Jos the Plateau state capital. Senator Daduut in a statement made available to newsmen in Josurged the newly Inaugurated officials of the party to work assiduously to take the party to higher heights. Dadu’ut advised the newly- inaugurated exco of her party not to concentrate their energy only at the party office but move to the rural communities to mobilise support for the party. Senator Dadu’ut, a Professor of French pledged to support the party at all times. She commended the Plateau state Governor Simon Lalong for the good works he is doing in Plateau and promised to always support him at all times.